definitions.definition: One of several species of sea birds of the genus Puffinus , especially, Ardenna gravis (syn. Puffinus gravis , Puffinus major ), the great shearwater , and Puffinus stricklandi , the black hagdon or sooty shearwater .

main_definition: ( regional , now rare ) One of several species of sea birds of the genus Puffinus , especially, Ardenna gravis (syn. Puffinus gravis , Puffinus major ), the great shearwater , and Puffinus stricklandi , the black hagdon or sooty shearwater .
